specification:
Person was a citizen for 10 years, lost citizenship otherwise than by withdrawal, and is resident in Austria. Administrative infractions are not relevant for the criminal record.; Other conditions: see mode A06.;
Person lost citizenship, otherwise than by withdrawal, while a minor is legally present in Austria and requests reacquisition of citizenship at the age 18 or 19. Other conditions: see mode A06.
Person lost citizenship due to acquisition of citizenship of another country by spousal extension or spousal transfer and applies for reacquisition of citizenship within 5 years after the end of marriage. Other conditions: see mode A06.

Person is born abroad to a citizen who was born in Belgium.;
Person is born abroad to a citizen who was born abroad (by declaration within five years after birth). 
(Automatic acquisition if person has not acquired citizenship of another country at the age of 18.)

Person has special achievements in the economic sphere is exempted from the A06 material conditions.;
Person invested 1 million BGN or similar as specified in the Foreigners Act and the Investment Promotion Act becomes citizen after 5 year of permanent residence and no convictions without renunciation and knowledge of Bulgarian.; 
Since 2015 person increased the investment to 2 million becomes a citizen after 1 year only.

Person is born abroad to a citizen in the service of Brazil.;

Person is born abroad to a citizen not in the service of Brazil and is registered with the Brazilian consulate.;

Person is born abroad to a citizen not in the service of Brazil and establishes residence in Brazil (by declaration after reaching the age of majority).

Person is a child born after 16 August 1960 to a deceased citizen. Provision also applies if parent was not a citizen but was entitled to become one. If person is permanently resident abroad, he/she must be registered as a citizen.;
Person is the spouse or widower or widow of a citizen, or was the spouse of a person who, if he or she had not passed away, would have become or would have been 
entitled to become a citizen. Other conditions: see A08.

Person is an emigrant of German ethnic origin from Eastern Europe who has suffered from discrimination due to his or her descent, who has admission to Germany and has obtained a special certificate.; 
Person is a citizen from another area in Europe (not Eastern Europe) where German is the official or colloquial language and has been resident in Germany for 4 years, or person is an emigrant of German ethnic origin and resident abroad. Other conditions: see A06.; 
Person is an ethnic German who was displaced as a member of the German army in 1945 and did not acquire another citizenship, or person is resident in Germany and was previously excluded from collective naturalisations for racial reasons. Other conditions: see A06.

Person is a minor who is adopted by a citizen, can maintain the nationality of origin if so established by the legal system of the country of origin. Other conditions: see mode A06.;
Person is an adult, or the citizenship application is made 2 years after the adoption. Other conditions: see mode A06.; 
Person is, or has been, under legal guardianship of a citizen appointed by the state to act as parent of an individual in need of protection. Other conditions: see mode A06.; 
Person has been subject to guardianship of a citizen or public institution in Spain for at least 2 years and has been resident there for 1 year.  Other conditions: see mode A06.

Person is born in Finland out of wedlock to a father who is a citizen and whose paternity of the child is established (FIN 9(1)(2)-(3)).;
Person is born abroad and out of wedlock to a father who has been a citizen since the person's birth and whose paternity is established before the marriage between the child's parents is contracted. In this case, person acquires citizenship as of the date when the marriage was contracted. If paternity is established after the marriage was contracted but before the person reaches the age of 18, citizenship is acquired as of the date when the paternity was established (FIN11).;
Person is born in Finland out of wedlock to a father who was a citizen at the time of the person's birth, and whose paternity was established after the person reaches the age of 18 or gets married, or the person is born outside Finland out of wedlock to a father who  was a citizen at the time of the person's birth, and whose paternity was established (FIN 26). What is said about the father whose paternity is established in Sections 9(1)(2)(b), 9(1)(3)(b) and 26 also applies to mother whose maternity is established under the Maternity Act (253/2018).

Person is born in France and has been resident there for 5 years since the age of 11.; 

Person is a minor who was born in France and has been resident there for 5 years since the age of 11 (declaration by child), or child is under the age of 16 and has been resident in France for 5 years since the age of 8 (declaration by parent).;

Person is born in Mayotte (France), has been resident there for 5 years since the age of 11, and has at least one parent legally residing in France for more than three months at the moment of birth.; 

Person is a minor who was born in Mayotte (France), and has been resident there for 5 years since the age of 11 (declaration by child), or child is under the age of 16 and has been resident in France for 5 years since the age of 8 (declaration by parent). In both cases, the person shall have at least one parent legally residing in France for more than three months at the moment of birth.

Person is born in the UK, is 10 years or older and resided in the UK during the first 10 years after birth (maximum absence from the UK for 90 days any one year). Other condition: good character.;
General discretion to register any minor.;
Child born in UK whose parents become settled (permanent residents) during minority may apply to register.;
Child born in UK whose parent joins armed forces during minority may apply to register.

Person is a former citizen and resident in Hungary. Other conditions: clean criminal record, no threat to Hungarian interests, and knowledge of Hungarian language.; 
Person was deprived or released from citizenship between 1946 and 1990.;
Person has renounced Hungarian citizenship but cannot acquire another citizenship and claims to restore Hungarian citizenship within 3 years

Person is a minor, born in Latvia after August 21, 1991 both whose parents are stateless persons (or comparable status 'non-citizens') and the parents have permanent residence in Latvia (with permanent residence permit if arrived after 1 July 1992). Application does not need to be submitted by both parents.;
Person is a minor, born in Latvia after August 21, 1991, has been stateless (or comparable status: 'non-citizen') since birth, and is a permanent resident. Declaration until the age of 15 by legal representative(s) who is (are) also stateless, and has been resident in Latvia for 5 years. From age of 15 and until the age of 18: declaration by person under further condition that he/she is proficient in the language of Latvia (but exceptions under LAT 21), and has not been sentenced for committing a serious crime.;
Person is a minor, born in Latvia after 1 January 2020, both of whose parents are 'non-citizens' , unless the parents have agreed on citizenship of another state or the child is a citizen of another country.;
Person is a minor, born outside Latvia after 1 January 2020 or whose one parent is a citizen of another country and one of whom has non-citizen status. Parents must submit an application for the grant of Latvian citizenship and affirm that the child is not and has not been a citizen of any other country and submit a document issued by a competent authority confirming that the child is not and has not been a citizen of the specific country.

Person is born abroad to two citizens, or to one parent who is a citizen and the other parent is unknown, stateless or of unknown citizenship.;
Person is born abroad to a citizen (registration by parent before the age of 18), or the person starts residing in Macedonia before the age of 18.; 
Person is born abroad to a citizen (declaration between the age of 18 and 23).

Person is born abroad to two citizens, or to one parent who is a citizen and another parent who is unknown, stateless or of unknown citizenship, or to one parent who is a citizen and the person would otherwise be stateless.;

Person is born abroad to a citizen and the person does not hold citizenship of another country (by registration by parent before the age of 18).;

Person is born abroad to a citizen (by declaration by person between the age of 18 and 23).

Person is an internationally famous personality and is born in and resident in Romania, or has been resident there for 4 years. Other conditions: see A06.; 
Person is granted 'honorary citizenship' by Parliament for making a special contribution to the country. No other conditions. Person enjoys all civil and political rights (except run for election and hold public office).;
Person has promoted Romania's culture or would represent the country in international sport competitions.

